	(text "Solenoid driver — 12V peak-and-hold, low-side N-FET.  PLACED, not wired.\nRAIL: VSOL(+12V) from PWR sheet.  C5 220uF (electrolytic) + C6 22uF reservoir on VSOL -> supplies the pull-in surge.\nSOLENOID J3 (JST-PH): 1 = VSOL(+12V)   2 = SOL_DRV (Q1 drain).\nD3 SS34 FLYBACK across the coil: anode = SOL_DRV, cathode = VSOL  (clamps the coil's collapse to VSOL + ~0.5V).\nQ1 AO3400A low-side N-FET (SOT-23, logic-level): 1 G <- R5 100R <- SOL_PWM ;  2 S -> GND ;  3 D -> SOL_DRV.\n   R6 100k gate->GND: holds Q1 OFF through reset / power-up / while the MCU sleeps (the lock cannot self-fire).\nPEAK-AND-HOLD (firmware on U1): SOL_BOOST_EN=1 -> wait VSOL settle -> SOL_PWM 100% pull-in (~20-50 ms)\n   -> drop PWM duty for HOLD (~1/3, tune to the coil) -> on release SOL_PWM=0 then SOL_BOOST_EN=0.\nSNUBBER (optional, DNP): R9 10R + C7 1nF from SOL_DRV -> GND; fit at bring-up only if drain ringing is high."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12.00 95.00 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.5 1.5)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "e8df9ca2-3733-4b67-8301-4227fd8cd6c0")
	)
	(sheet_instances
		(path "/"
			(page "4")
		)
	)
